  "commit_message": "[turbopack] Use `final_read_hint` in top level turbo tasks (#94712)\n\nUse `final_read_hint` on top level turbo tasks\n\nFor many top level tasks where we are returning data there is no need for turbo-tasks to hold on to it afterwars, but these are typically also _transient_ and thus un-evictable.  So use the `final_read_hint` to allow turbo tasks to drop the cell after reading it.\n\nThe biggest impact here is HmrUpdateWithIssues that holds a potentially large hmr instruction.\n\nFrom a simple benchmar",
